A Northern Cape teenager has been handed a hefty sentence. The 17-year-old boy was sentenced on three counts; robbery
aggravating, murder and rape. The accused was found guilty and sentenced by the Northern
Cape High Court on Saturday, 11 June, 2022. Police Spokesperson, Captain Olebogeng Tawana said, “In July
2021 the accused accosted a 81-year-old elderly woman, at her home in Cassel
village where he raped, murdered and robbed her of her belongings. “The accused was arrested and the investigating officer
Lieutenant Colonel Doggy Magugu successfully opposed bail, and he was kept in
police custody until the finalisation of trial. The accused was found guilty and sentenced as follows; Count 1, Robbery Aggravating- 15 years imprisonment; Count 2, Murder- 18 year’s imprisonment; Count 3, Rape - 18 years imprisonment. READ: School principal nabbed for rape Tawana said the sentences were ordered to run concurrently.
The accused will serve effective 18 years imprisonment. The Acting Deputy Provincial Commissioner for Crime
Detection, Brigadier Nicky Mills commended Lieutenant Colonel Doggy Magugu for
excellent investigative work. The Northern Cape High Court declared the accused unfit to
possess a firearm, and ordered that his name be entered in the National Sex
Offenders Register.